x4freetext: The detector telescope used to observe
the scattered particles subtended a solid angle of
2.50x10 sr. It consisted of a transmission-type
surface-barrier delta E detector and a
lithium-drifted silicon E detector. The delta E
detector was 100 microm thick, operated with a
reverse bias of 20 V, and the E detector was 2000
microm thick, operated with a reverse bias of 500 V.
Both detectors were cooled by thermoelectric devices
to -30 C to minimize leakage currents. The
particle-identification circuit was used to select
A beam of 17.85-MeV 3He particles was momentum
analyzed by a 90 degree bending magnet with a 76.2-cm
radius of curvature, focused to a spot at the center
of a 60.9-cm-diam scattering chamber. The beam was
monitored by a Faraday cup and current digitizer.
